{\*\bkmkstart Charity_fundraiser_Sun_1_June_}Twenty{\*\bkmkend Charity_fundraiser_Sun_1_June_}-four hours earlier, on a beautiful Sunday night in California, a crowd of well-dressed couples are streaming into the Palo Alto Event Center.\
\
Inside, a view screen fills one side of the entry hall. Playing on the wall is a montage of the good works of the Palo Alto Big Siblings Club: \'93Adults who care, a meal you can count on.\'94\
\
A handful of people are greeting guests as they arrive.\
\
\'93Elena, I\'92m so glad you came,\'94 greets Heather. Her blonde hair, blue eyes, and white dress glisten against a backdrop of dark suits and gowns.\
\
\'93I wouldn\'92t miss one of your fundraisers, Heather. The club helped me so much after my parentals passed. \'97 You remember 
\f1\i mi esposa
\f0\i0 , Tessa.\'94 Elena gestures toward her companion.\
\
Tessa\'92s dark skin complements Elena\'92s warm brown complexion. They wear demure evening gowns, which match without being \'93matchy\'94. Elena\'92s heels are two inches taller than Tessa\'92s, bringing their height closer together.\
\
  All three women have styled their hair with careful elegance and expensive hair extensions.\
\
\'93Of course. Head of testing at Pulse, as I remember,\'94 says Heather. \'93You two may be my favorite power couple.\'94 She smiles brightly at Tessa and then looks toward Elena. \'93I\'92m so glad the club could help. As the treasurer, I can say that your company\'92s ongoing generosity makes a difference.\'94 \
\
A server bot rolls up, carrying a tray of champagne. All three women take a glass.\
\
Heather smiles again. \'93I see you swimming in the morning, Elena. Are the prosthetics helping?\'94\
\
\'93I still use them to walk from the locker room to the pool and for special occasions, like tonight. But at home and work, I have to say I prefer the chair. I suffer migraines when I use the neural link for too long.\'94\
\
Helen frowns and says, \'93That must be difficult.\'94 \
\
\'93I do like the chair. It practically drives itself, and it has more safety features than our car. \'97 I can still use the link whenever I want. Just not too much.\'94\
\
\'93My older sibling, Gage, can\'92t tolerate any type of brain-computer interface,\'94 says Heather. \'93Sometimes I feel frustrated by all the regulations that call for non-link options. Then I think of my big sib.\'94\
\
Tessa asks Heather, \'93How is your day job at the YPCA doing? I see your \'91All In\'92 spots come up on my Pulse health hub almost every day.\'94\
\
\'93Only 
\f1\i almost
\f0\i0 ! \'97 I\'92ll have to tweak our settings,\'94 jokes Heather. All three smile and sip from their glasses together. \
\
A photo drone descends and hovers in front of the three women. Heather looks to Elena for approval. She then nods to the drone and leans into the couple for the click op. \
\
The drone drops the photo onto their phones and slips away. \'93Speaking of Pulse,\'94 Heather says, \'93my association referrals improved all of a sudden. Are you tweaking the algorithm?\'94\
\
Elena smiles. \'93
\f1\i \'a1Todos los d\'edas!
\f0\i0  \'97 Every day! I\'92ll pass along the praise to our engineers. It\'92s a popular feature. A lot of people use referrals to expand their colleague circle.\'94\
\
Elena, Tessa, and Heather nod and smile good bye. The couple continue past Heather into the main room. \
\
Heather moves off to greet another couple. She casually points her phone in their direction. On the screen, the contact notes are still open to Elena Vargas. 
\f1\i \'93Chief Experience Officer at Pulse Social Media. Swims in the morning. Prosthetics. Lost parentals in car accident. Spouse is Tessa, Pulse Chief Quality Officer.\'94
\f0\i0 \
\
Her phone recognizes the other couple from her contact list and updates the screen. Siri sends the background notes that Heather keeps on major donors to her implant.\
\
Heather smiles and waves hello. Catching their eye, she welcomes her patrons with a group text through their implants. The server bot follows her across the room.\
\
