Throughout the evening, other guests come up to the Pulse table praising the association algorithm. The Chief Technical Officer, Adrian Cho, is also at the table, looking uncomfortable in a tux too tight for his muscular frame.\
\
After the third or fourth comment, Adrian reaches over the table to tap Elena\'92s hand. Getting her attention, he touches his temple. Elena nods and activates her implant.\
\
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f1\i \cf0 \'93Did we make some kind of change, Elena? I noticed the difference myself.\'94 \
\
\'93Not that I\'92m aware. I\'92ll check with Brent in the morning.\'94
\f0\i0 \
\
During the cyber auction, Tessa makes a few modest bids over her link, without success.\
\
On the way home, Tessa says, \'93I see what Heather means about the association feed. It\'92s not only suggesting people I know but also people I might 
\f1\i want
\f0\i0  to know and 
\f1\i why
\f0\i0  I might like to know them. Ally is comparing everything with everything else. Posts, comments, photos, resumes \'97 not just colleagues. You should check it out.\'94\
\
\'93I don\'92t remember approving a change like that. Did your team test it?\'94\
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
Tessa shakes her head. \'93First I\'92ve heard of it. Should you call Brent?\'94\
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\'93I\'92m just too tired right now, Tess. The neural link wore me out tonight. I\'92ll let you know what he says in the morning. Adrian seemed okay with it.\'94 Elena shuts her eyes, content to be a passenger.\
\
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0
