\cf0 \'93{\*\bkmkstart Park_and_Tate_report_their_fin}I{\*\bkmkend Park_and_Tate_report_their_fin} just don\'92t know, Lieutenant,\'94 says Park. \
\
The agents stand near an office doorway. Frosted windows and walnut trim line the office. Inside the room, a fit person with thinning grey hair is sitting behind an ancient wooden desk. \
\
Park goes on, \'93We can\'92t find a mechanical cause, and Geller didn\'92t seem to have any personal issues. He had a healthy bank account balance. His credit card was always paid in full. According to his sibling, Geller vacationed in a different country every year for vacation. He played softball and online games, took holidays, and worked. \'97 Life of Riley.\'94\
\
Park regrets her choice of words. The news of Brent\'92s death the day before reached them as the Thursday morning meeting started.\
\
\'93Geller made a mistake at work,\'94 Park continues. \'93Some experimental code escaped the laboratory, but everyone is loving the experiment.\'94 \
\
\'93The coincidence with his boss\'92s wheelchair is still weird,\'94 says Tate. \'93That and the missing phone.\'94\
\
\'93Wheelchair?\'94 asks Lieutenant Callahan. \'93Is this one of your tangents, Tate?\'94\
\
Calmly, Tate looks Callahan in his green Irish eyes. \'93His boss, Elena Vargas, uses a wheelchair. The night of Brent\'92s crash, Elena Vargas was tossed into an endless pool by her very high-end wheelchair.\'94\
\
\'93Endless pool?\'94\
\
\'93It\'92s like a meter deep. You swim against a current created with water jets. Like a treadmill for swimming. A Jacuzzi turned sideways.\'94\
\
\'93Hmm. I don\'92t know about the chair,\'94 says Callahan. \'93It\'92s more likely that the contraption slipped on some wet tile. It\'92s the airbag failing to deploy that bothers me. A body flying through the windshield is not a good visual. Was Geller in the habit of not wearing a safety harness?\'94\
\
Park says, \'93His sibling said that Brent would engage the harness as soon as the beeping started. If not sooner. Like anyone else.\'94\
\
\'93So one scenario is that the car decided to lurch forward on its own. It disengaged the harness and disabled the airbag. The other scenario is that Geller unclipped his harness and punched the accelerator. But that doesn\'92t explain why the airbag didn\'92t deploy.\'94\
\
\'93If the event data recorder wasn\'92t blank, then we would know,\'93 says Park. \'93But it\'92s like the car recorded nothing since the day it rolled off the lot. There are a lot of missing pieces.\'94\
\
Tate says, \'93We could still get a court order for the phone\'92s cloud data. It might tell us if Geller tried to brake before the crash, or if he was using his phone when the car accelerated.\'94\
\
\'93I don\'92t think the phone data will help us,\'94 says Callahan. \'93I\'92m worried about the airbag failure.\'94\
\
\'93It\'92s possible that the airbag is defective,\'93 says Park. \'93There was a recall for a prior model, but nothing specific for this model yet. The manufacturer says it\'92s been tested throughly, but they always say that.\'94\
\
\'93I did examine the airbag from the crash,\'94 says Tate, \'93and I don\'92t see any reason why it would 
\f1\i not
\f0\i0  deploy.\'94\
\
\'93Were you able to track down the reports by witnesses of a drone at the scene?\'94\
\
\'93We were able to get dashcam footage from one witness,\'93 says Park. \'93There is a blur on the screen, but I can\'92t say for sure that it was a drone. Even so, there are drones flying everywhere all the time.\'94\
\
\'93I don\'92t like it,\'94 grumbles Callahan, \'93but the last clear chance to avoid injury was for the airbag to deploy. Write it up as Unconfirmed Mechanical Failure, blame the bag for the injuries, and move on.\'94\
\
\'93Then could we move on to the wheelchair failure?\'94 asks Tate, ignoring the frown on Park\'92s face. \'93Essentially, it\'92s a single-passenger vehicle. The electronics can be as complicated as a car. The best ones cost more than a motorcycle.\'94\
\
