{\*\bkmkstart Jills_kid_is_ready_for_an_impl}Jill{\*\bkmkend Jills_kid_is_ready_for_an_impl} Kreuk, home after a long day at OSSA headquarters, paces back and forth across the polished hardwood floor of her living room.\
\
The Thursday afternoon sun bathes the room in a soft, golden glow. The light does nothing to calm the gnawing anxiety spreading out from her chest. She clutches a cup of tea in one hand. It has long since gone cold. Her spouse, Peter, sits on the couch, watching her with quiet concern. His phone lies abandoned on the living room table.\
\
 \'93I don\'92t know, Peter,\'94 Jill says out loud. \'93There are so many parental decisions. First, it\'92s vaccines. Then it\'92s tablets, passwords, pierced ears, cosmetics, explaining periods. Soon it will be tattoos and smart glasses. For Patrick, it was to circumcise or not, the robot dog fiasco, standing up to bullies, when no means no.\'94\
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \'93Now it\'92s whether to put an implant behind our kid\'92s ear. \'97 This is a huge step. What if it\'92s too much for her?\'94 \
\
Jill pauses to take a deep breath. She links, \'93
\f1\i A neural link and a phone? She\'92s only twelve.\'94\
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\partightenfactor0
