\cf0 	\'93{\*\bkmkstart Investigators_meet_with_store_}Welcome{\*\bkmkend Investigators_meet_with_store_} to Porto Mobility. Can I help you?\'94 \
\
	The showroom is a long rectangle, with the door on one side, next to a large pane window. Parallel to the door are lines of wheelchairs, each with its own design. There are black, red, green, and purple chairs. Not one is blue and orange. A stuffed pooh bear is sitting in one of the green chairs. On one side, behind the wheelchairs, is a selection of power lift recliners.\
\
	The greeter\'92s name tag reads \'93Aubrey, Store Manager\'94. Under the name tag is a lapel button with a QR code for access to the store\'92s link account.\
\
	Ignoring the QR code, Park flashes her badge. \'93We\'92re from the California Transportation Safety Board. I\'92d like to ask you about Elena Vargas\'92s wheelchair.\'94\
\
	\'93Yes, I have it in the back. I have no idea what went wrong. Ms. Vargas is on a FullCare plan, so we gave her a new one. \'97 I know you handle car collisions, like the one on El Camino Real this week. Is the CTSB investigating wheelchairs now?\'94\
\
	\'93We\'92re investigating this one,\'94 says Tate. \'93May I see the chair, please?\'94\
\
	\'93Let me call corporate first. This wasn\'92t covered in my training.\'94\
\
	The agents know they are on shaky ground. A police report usually gives CTSB jurisdiction. They checked on the way over, but Elena hadn\'92t reported the incident, and it was (after all) a wheelchair. The investigators wait while the store manager calls corporate. \
\
	\'93They say you need a warrant.\'94\
\
	\'93Could you hand me the phone, please?\'94 asks Tate, holding out his hand.\
\
	\'93Hello, this is government agent Ben Tate. I can go to a judge and get a warrant for the wheelchair. But that will create a public record that the news networks could pick up. The Chief Experience Officer of Pulse Social Media being dumped into her pool by your chair might make for a juicy news item. For now, I only want to visually inspect the chair.\'94 Tate listened for a moment and handed the phone back to the store manager.\
\
	Aubrey lowers the phone. \'93Legal says you can look at the chair but not remove it from the premises.\'94\
\
	\'93I\'92m good with that,\'94 says Tate.\
\
	\'93Can I get you some coffee or anything, agents? Glacier water?\'94\
\
