	\'93Not really. I mean, if test mode were engaged, someone could override the safeties and run the chair into a curb. But you need a special console to use test mode.\'94\
\
	\'93Do you have one of the consoles?\'94\
\
	\'93Yes, we use it for demonstrations. Just a second.\'94\
\
	The manager goes out front and returns with a device that looks like a gaming console, along with a pair of smart glasses.\
\
	\'93That chair is inoperable now, but I have another one here that we can use. I need to scan the serial number first.\'94\
\
	The manager tips up the chair and peers under the seat with her smart glasses. Lowering the chair, she uses the console to move the chair around the backroom.\
\
	\'93The chair usually stops before it runs into anything, the same as any bot would.\'94 Aubrey points the chair at a box. It beeps and stops before hitting the obstacle. \'93But I can override and let the chair hit something.\'94 She puts the chair in reverse, touches some controls. It moves slowly forward again. This time the chair doesn\'92t beep. It bumps into the box.\
\
	\'93Is there any way I can get one of these consoles?\'94\
\
	\'93Not really. We don\'92t sell them. The range is only a few feet.\'94\
\
	\'93Thank you, Aubrey,\'94 says Park. \'93We\'92ll be in touch if there is anything further.\'94\
\
	As they were leaving, Aubrey says, removing her smart glasses, \'93You know some cars have a test mode now too.\'94\
\
	\'93What do you mean?\'94 asks Tate. \'93Since when? That sounds dangerous.\'94\
\
	\'93There are protections. First, you need to plug a special dongle into the car. Then you can program an app on your device to control a self-driving car the same way we controlled the wheelchair.\'94\
\
	\'93Dongle?\'94 asks Park.\
\
	\'93Umm, an OBD, I think it\'92s called.\'94\
\
	\'93On Board Diagnostic connector?\'94 asks Tate.\
\
	\'93Yeah, that\'92s it. \'97 I worked for a car company before I came here. We\'92re not suppose to talk about it \'85 but I\'92m not suppose to withhold information from government agents either \'85\'94\
\
	Tate nods, taking the hint. \'93Please tell us what you know about test mode.\'94\
\
	\'93The manufacturers run sophisticated tests through the connector when the cars are being developed,\'94 Aubrey explains. \'93Self-driving cars make companies paranoid about liability. They lock down everything \'97 diagnostics, telemetry, event recorders, test mode \'97 because one bad headline can tank a stock.\'94\
\
	\'93You mean cars like a Stratos could have a test mode?\'94 asks Park.\
\
	\'93Yes. It\'92s fairly recent and kept on the down-low. My supervisor used to say that \'91The first rule of test mode is that we don\'92t talk about test mode\'92.\'94 Aubrey pauses and adds: \'93But if it were used, it would show up on the event data recorder.\'94\
