\'93Mom, stop,\'94says Julie. \'93It\'92s a simple procedure. I don\'92t even have to change into a gown. It\'92s one step above having my ears pierced.\'94 \
\
Julie\'92s pageboy haircut shows off her ears. Each ear has three piercings. The rows of silver earrings complement the blue and purple streaks in her platinum hair. \
\
\'93I know, dear. I\'92m a mom. Mom\'92s worry.\'94\
\
The door to the small examination room opens. The nurse practitioner joins them.\
\
\'93Big day,\'94 says Darlene. \'93Are you ready for your first implant?\'94\
\
Julie nods. Vigorously. Jill says, \'93Offspring is ready. I am not.\'94\
\
\'93There\'92s nothing to worry about,\'94 Darlene says, smiling. \'93We inject chips all the time. A bot could do it, but we like the personal touch. \'97 Is the phone ready to go with the Link app?\'94\
\
\'93Yes, we unboxed it, installed the app, and set up the parental controls.\'94\
\
\'93OK, good to go then.\'94 The medbot had left a metal tray carrying a syringe in a sealed plastic bag with a white backing. Darlene opens the bag and removes a small card from inside. She picks up a small instrument with a gray screen from the tray. Darlene scans the syringe, compares the screen with the card, and nods. Then she hands the card to Jill.\
\
\'93Keep this card in a safe place. It has the link\'92s serial number. We\'92ll need it to program the phone in a minute.\'94 The card has a QR code on one side and a UPC on the other side.\
\
\'93The QR code will take you to the manufacturer\'92s website, where you can check the warranty and other information.\'94\
\
\'93But it\'92s plug and play, right?\'94 asks Julie. \'93I\'92ll be able to use it today?\'94\
\
\'93Yes. You should wait at least an hour. Then you will be all set.\'94\
\
\'93And after we have gone over how to use the link safely,\'93 says Jill.\
\
\'93I already checked her chart, but I\'92m required to ask if Juliette has any allergies to chlorhexidine.\'94\
\
Julie shakes her head. \'93No allergies.\'94\
\
The nurse practitioner holds back Julie\'92s hair. There is a swab on the tray, which Darlene uses to prepare the injection area. \'93We need to wait thirty-five seconds. Don\'92t touch the area or move your head.\'94 The swabbed area turns red as the antiseptic spreads. Then it begins to clear.\
\
Darlene checks her watch. A few seconds later, she says \'93OK, let\'92s do this thing.\'94 Darlene picks up the syringe from the tray.\
\
The plastic syringe is short and stout. Its stem has two sturdy,  rounded handles. The business end is larger than a typical instrument. Darlene removes a cap, exposing the tip, which is crosscut at a slant. \'93There will be a pinch.\'94 She presses the syringe into Julie\'92s neck. Then the nurse pulls back on the handles together, releasing the chip.\
\
Julie winces. \'93Sorry,\'94 says Darlene, \'93but it\'92s over now.\'94 The nurse practitioner picks up the scanner again. The scanner beeps, confirming that the chip is working.\
\
\'93Do you have the phone?\'94\
\
Jill pulls the new phone from her purse. \'93Can you bring up the Link app?\'94 Darlene asks. Jill nods, touching the screen. \'93Now use the camera to scan the UPC on the card.\'94 Jill holds up the card, and the phone bleeps. \'93Can you show me the screen?\'94 Jill turns the device around, Darlene peers and the screen and says, \'93All set. You can close the app now.\'94\
\
Darlene looks at Julie and says, \'93Wait an hour before you try to use the link. Then your mom will get you started.\'94 Turning her head, she says to Jill, \'93After an hour, check for any redness, and open the app again. It will walk through a setup wizard. Then you can get her started with the link. Give us a call right away if there is any redness or swelling.\'94\
\
Looking at both of them together, Darlene smiles and says, \'93Exciting!\'94\
