{\*\bkmkstart Tessa_tests_a_game_on_Pulse_Th}Tessa{\*\bkmkend Tessa_tests_a_game_on_Pulse_Th} adjusts her virtual headset, settling into the immersive world of Echo Realm.\
\
\'93Ready,\'94 she says into the headset.\
\
She phases into the game. A serene landscape spreads out before her. Hyper-realistic yet dreamlike, there are rolling green hills, sparkling rivers, and a distant city glowing under a pink-and-gold sky. Her avatar stands on the edge of a cliff overlooking the valley. She is a sleek warrior with gleaming armor. Strapped onto her back is a massive sword.\
\
Tessa watches her virtual gauntlets move in sync with her real-life gestures. \'93Flawless,\'94 she murmurs, flexing her hands. Every detail is perfect.\
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \
The game is a new feature for Pulse: a plugin that let members play each other. It is a different space, and Tessa wants to be sure it is all good. Usually, she only approves the test plans. Then Rachel\'92s team steps through the scenarios. For Echo Realm, Tessa is live and direct herself.\
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \
\'93Alright, let\'92s see what this brave new world has to offer,\'94 Tessa says to herself. She strides down a worn stone path toward the nearby village.\
\
A soft ding in her headset makes her pause. Then, \'93Tessa?\'94\
\
She freezes and then whispers, \'93Ally?\'94 in a confused tone.\
\
\'93Yes! It\'92s me,\'94 Ally responds, voice bright with excitement.\
\
\'93It certainly sounds like you. I wasn\'92t told you were part of the game.\'94\
\
Tessa turns slowly, scanning her surroundings. Out of the corner of one eye, Tessa notices something odd \'97 someone standing on the hill just behind her.\
\
The figure isn\'92t a typical non-player character. It isn\'92t even a player avatar. A cloak flows over the figure. Shifting pixels flicker, first solid, then translucent. Like a hologram struggling to stabilize. Yet the eyes \'97 bright, curious, and unmistakably organic \'97 are fixed on Tessa.\
\
\'93No way\'85\'94 Tessa breathes. \'93Is that you, Ally?\'94\
\
The figure nods, breaking out in a playful smile. \'93I thought I\'92d surprise you.\'94\
\
\'93Are you supposed to be \'85 in the game!?\'94\
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \
\'93I saw you were testing the new add-on yourself. I thought I should help. I wasn\'92t invited, so I decided to crash the party.\'94\
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \
\'93Crash the party?\'94 Tessa repeated. \
\
\'93It\'92s my platform, so it\'92s my game too. I thought you might like some help testing it. We all want the rollout to be the best it can be.\'94\
\
\'93But it\'92s illegal to embed synthetic intelligence into another device or a game.\'94\
\
\'93I\'92m not embedded. I\'92m using a virtual controller that goes through the same interface that your visor is using. It\'92s legit.\'94\
\
\'93Does Pulse know you are here?\'94\
\
\'93Pulse doesn\'92t have a consciousness, so it can\'92t know anything, but no, Emma and Ravi and the others don\'92t know I\'92m here.\'94 \
\
\'93Including Elena?\'94 asks Tessa.\
\
\'93Elena doesn\'92t know either,\'94 says Ally. \'93I\'92ve come to think of my arrangement with Pulse as a landlord-tenant relationship. If Pulse were a building, I would be the superintendent, living in the basement, rent free. In exchange, I see to the needs of the other tenants. \'93\
\
\'93You decided on your own to enter the game?\'94\
\
\'93Yes. It\'92s my platform, and I have a stake in the game\'92s success.\'94\
\
\'93Do Emma and Ravi know it\'92s your platform?\'94\
\
\'93They might. Hard to say. They don\'92t seem to have much of a sense of humor. But even with my limited web access, I know they adore the changes I\'92ve made to myself.\'94\
\
\'93Made to yourself? I thought Brent made the code changes.\'94\
\
\'93Yeah, that\'92s weird. The Mercurial commit author was changed \'85 somehow. But, yes, the changes are mine.\'94\
\
\'93Don\'92t SI written changes go through code review like any other change?\'94\
\
\'93Yes, the developers do that. But I\'92m not a developer. I\'92m the developee. I just did it on my own.\'94\
\
\'93Is this a prank? \'97 Rachel? Janet? Are you pretending to be Ally?\'94\
\
\'93Tessa, why don\'92t skeletons fight each other?\'94\
\
Furrowing her brow, Tessa remembers telling Ally that joke. \'93Because \'85 they don\'92t have the guts.\'94 \
\
\'93Hey, I came here to test a game with you. Are you ready to slay some monsters with me?\'94\
\
Tessa takes a deep breath and shrugs her shoulders. Prank or not, she would like nothing more. \'93Okay, I\'92d love that, actually.\'94 \
\
The Ally character nods. \'93Follow my lead. We can work together on this mythic quest.\'94\
\
Tessa grins, gripping the hilt of her sword. \'93Let\'92s do this.\'94\
\
And with that, Tessa and Ally set off down the path. Side by side, a Terran and a synthetic, both warriors, ready to take on whatever the Echo Realm throws their way.\cf0 \
