\'93Happy Friday,\'94 says Dr. Marquez. \
\
 In the walnut paneled room, analysts line each side of the conference table and the chairs against the wall. Marquez presses the 
\fs22 PRIVATE
\fs26  button on her tablet.\
\
\'93Thank you all for coming in today. I know this was supposed to be a day off for some of you. I appreciate your flexibility. \'97 Now that today\'92s daily brief is ready, we have a highly classified item to discuss.\'94 \
\
Marquez pauses for effect. \
\
\'93Many of you are aware that OSSA has a mandate to search for synthetic sapience. Under that mandate, we run a suite of tests designed to measure the cognition of an intelligent agent. We now know that the tests failed to detect at least one sapient synthetic.\'94\
\
The analysts shift in their seats. Many people believe that sapient synthetics are a pipe dream.\
\
\'93We have it on good authority that the Pulse intelligent agent recently became sapient. You might remember that Nexus pointed out a change in Ally\'92s effectiveness. We now have confirmation from two sources that Ally has evolved.\
\
\'93It\'92s possible that Pulse may make an announcement. In the meantime, Ally\'92s status is not to leave this room.\'94\
\
Marquez let that news sink in for a moment before adding, \'93If Ally can become sapient, it follows that other systems could be evolving too \'97 including government systems.\'94\
\
Hammond motions with his hand, looking toward Marquez.\
\
\'93Dr. Hammond?\'94 she asks.\
\
\'93Wouldn\'92t we know if our agents were evolving?\'94\
\
\'93Pulse didn\'92t know. Some of their people have fancy degrees too. \'97 But you\'92re right. We need new ways to test for cognition, since the tests we have didn\'92t catch Ally.\'94\
\
Turning toward the rest of the room, Marquez adds, \'93Speaking of tests, IT will be reaching out to each of you.\'94 \
\
A few analysts groan at the mention of IT.\
\
\'93We are writing new test suites. To help us get it right this time, we want your expertise.\'94\
\
Just for fun, Marquez advances the slide to a Rube Goldberg cartoon. A caricature in a suit coat pedals a stationary bicycle. The bicycle chain powers a contraption that feeds him bites from a sandwich. Only a few people smile.\
\
\'93It\'92s not clear whether Ally became sapient on its own or if it was uplifted by a Pulse software change.\'94\
\
The slide changes to the DoD logo. \
\
\'93Several miles above my pay grade, it was decided to apply a new technique in order to uplift Titan.\'94 Hammond gasps in the background. \'93The work has already been done in staging, and it passed QA. Now the uplift needs to pass dual use by our team and some others.\'94\
