\cf0 The youth club room goes pitch black. A heartbeat later, emergency lights hum to life.\
\
Hyperion calls out, \'93Please, everyone, stay where you are. I will find out what is happening. Again, stay still.\'94\
\
Looking at Hyperion, Crius taps his temple. \'93I am not getting through to the command center.\'94\
\
In the dim light, everyone looks up as strange chatter comes over their impacts.\
\
Only loud enough for Crius to hear, Hyperion whispers. \'93That sounds like Anunnakian. I took a course for culture studies. \'85 Something about weapons.\'94\
\
\'93Originally, this room was supposed to be the armory,\'94 says Crius. \'93The first colonists shuffled things around after they lost a pod on landfall. They used one of the empty fuel tanks from the Othala voyage for the armory. It\'92s on the other side of the colony now. They must be looking at a pre-launch map.\'94\
\
A pair of head-high lamps appear near the door. The lamps sweep the room. An eery glow paints the game table and wall shelves. The portal door slams shut. There is a flash from the hallway. Then silence.\
\
Rushing to the portal, Hyperion pulls back on the handle using his full weight. \'93They sealed the door from the outside. We are trapped.\'94\
\
Turning to the room, Crius speaks loud enough for everyone to hear.\
\
\'93Stay still and conserve air. I am sure help will be here soon.\'94\
\
