{\*\bkmkstart All_Aboard_}Elara{\*\bkmkend All_Aboard_} and Venn join sixty other passengers on a shuttle to the orbital docking station.\
\
The line to the ship is long, but it moves fast. Before long, the couple step through the docking airlock, holding hands. Three long fingers interlaced. The pressurized doors seal behind them with a soft hiss. \
\
The metallic interior of the colony ship is a welcome change from the cloudy, grey skies of Othala. Everything gleams with sterile efficiency. The floors are a seamless alloy. Modular panels line the walls. The panels pulse with the hum of life support systems.\
\
\'93This is \'85 massive,\'94 Elara murmurs. Her eyes trace the vaulted corridor overhead. Light strips run in clean, geometric patterns. \'93I cannot believe that this could be home.\'94\
\
\'93It will not feel so empty when it is full of people,\'94 Venn says, nudging her and smiling.\
\
A guide approached \'97 an older colonist named Mara. She is wearing the slate-gray uniform of the ship\'92s operations crew. \
\
Mara smiles broadly. She gestures toward the corridor ahead. \'93Welcome aboard. Would you like to start with the living quarters?\'94\
\
They follow her past several bulkhead doors marked with glowing symbols. Some doors open as they pass. Beyond the doors are glimpses of workstations, hydroponic bays, and storage modules. Each space optimized, every function tallied.\
\
The residential sector feels familiar. Rows of compact, comfortable apartments curve along the interior walls. Hexagonal doors lead into private quarters. A massive atrium peeks through a transparent ceiling panel. The colony\'92s central green space is bathed in the golden glow of artificial sunlight.\
\
\'93This is the recreation pod,\'94 Mara explains. She leads them onto an observation deck. The deck overlooks terraced gardens, water features, and small plazas designed for gathering.\
\
\'93We cannot bring the entire planet with us. So we recreated the essentials. And then some.\'94\
\
Venn leans against the railing. He gazes at the lush foliage of bio-engineered trees. A few colonists were already wandering the winding paths. \'93It is beautiful,\'94 he admits. \'93I was not expecting so much \'85 space.\'94\
\
Elara\'92s eyes locks on the far end of the atrium. A massive viewport reveals the distant glow of Othala\'92s star. Beyond it, the darkness of space stretches endlessly. \'93And that?\'94 she asks.\
\
\'93The launch bay,\'94 Mara says. \'93Right now, it is open to the world. But soon, it will be sealed for the journey. Once we leave, that bay will be the only way in or out.\'94\
\
A silence settles between them. The weight of what they are considering presses down like artificial gravity. The sheer finality of it.\
\
Venn glanced at Elara. \'93We would be leaving everything behind.\'94\
\
Elara meets his gaze, then she looks back at the colony ship. The self-sufficient world that would carry 24,000 people across the stars. \
\
\'93But we will have a future. A better life for our descendants. For our offspring.\
\
Mara smiles. \'93We are filling up fast. If you are applying, you will need to decide soon. Is there anyone else who might come with you? Cousins? Parentals? All ages are welcome.\'94\
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\'93No, it\'92s just us,\'94 says Elara.\
\
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Venn takes a long look at the glowing pathways and the towering walls. Then he exhales.\
\
\'93Where do we sign up?\'94\
\
