The overhead lights flash, then blink out. Brent\'92s shell melts into liquified goo. The internal organs dissolve into mites. In the dim red light of the 
\fs22 \cf5 EXIT
\fs26 \cf0  sign, a thousand mites push the goo from the edges of the body drawer into a hazardous waste drain. When the lights blink on, the room is pristine again. \
\
