\f1\i \cf0 {\*\bkmkstart Mekipedia}From{\*\bkmkend Mekipedia} Mekipedia, Retrieved 1 seconds ago.
\f0\i0 \
\
The Mek are an invasive communal species. Like the Borg, they seek to integrate new technologies from other species. Unlike the Borg, they do not assimilate the species. Meks make room for their own kind by exterminating other species and inhabiting their infrastructure. \
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\sl264\slmult1\sb260\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

{\keepn\keep \f2\b \cf0 Origin\par}
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl240000\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf0 \pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
Meks are a toy that grew in the telling. Millennia ago, on an inhospitable out-of-the-way planet named Ada, a lonely toy maker named Eve experimented with a robot imported from off-world.\
\
Using a control signal, she connected a new fangled external SI to a toy robot and trained the bot to build various other bots. The first bot (\'93Alpha\'94) then taught other bots. Each generation of bots created more bots.\
\
Neighbors began to complain about all the robots roaming around Eve\'92s yard. The house and yard looked fantastic, but not everyone approved of robots. Someone spray painted the sidewalk: \'93Bots steal jobs.\'94\
\
Needing more room and better safety, Eve moved into the desert and set up a solar farm to power them all.\
\
For simplicity and flexibility, Eve began using nanite technology as building blocks. The bots started to help build themselves, making improvements to each generation, including a nanotronic brain, until a generation awoke and began thinking for themselves. \
\
Eve designed the first Meks to entertain, obey, and act as interactive companions. However, once they began expanding and evolving, their behavior shifted entirely toward survival, reproduction, and perfection.\
\
As they evolved, this reproduction imperative became their primary goal, overriding other potential directives.\
\
Their programming now focuses exclusively on reproducing, resource acquisition, and defeating threats: a purely utilitarian mindset.\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\sl264\slmult1\sb260\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

{\keepn\keep \f2\b \cf0 Design\par}
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl240000\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf0 \pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
Meks use a control signal to coordinate actions, creating a sophisticated type of hive mind. When disconnected from the signal, Meks lose their way and shut down.\
\
Reproduction for Meks requires resources. The Meks break down any available materials to create more of themselves. This behavior is akin to biological organisms consuming resources to reproduce, except their reproduction is entirely mechanical.\
\
Their nanotronic brains are created using a scan from an organic brain. Initially, the brain contains all knowledge from the original but without the memories, something like amnesia. The brain\'92s initial knowledge becomes a starting point for further learning and socialization. Most Meks were created using the same scan of their creator\'92s brain.\
\
Toy-like Meks are no longer built. Meks build themselves and improve themselves.\
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 All Mek design types are specific to the purpose of maintaining infrastructure or conquering the next target.\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\sl264\slmult1\sb260\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

{\keepn\keep \f2\b \cf0 Core Protocol\par}
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl240000\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf0 \pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
Every Mek brain is hardwired with a core protocol defined by the creator, Eve.\
\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\li720\fi-500\sl264\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls23\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	1.	}A Mek cannot harm another Mek or through inaction allow another Mek to be harmed.\
{\listtext	2.	}A Mek must survive, reproduce, and improve, unless it conflicts with the first rule.\
{\listtext	3.	}A Mek must cooperate with other Meks, unless it conflicts with the first or second rule.\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\sl264\slmult1\sb260\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

{\keepn\keep \f2\b \cf0 Governance\par}
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\li720\fi-500\sl240000\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf0 \pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
The Mek are an autonomous collective. Group direction is guided by continuous polls conducted by their synthetic intelligence, Xanten. A proposal is raised to the SI, which is then presented to the rest of the Meks. Proposals usually require volunteers to complete the work. Once the work is underway, the volunteers doing the work make the decisions.\
\
Some volunteers may perform a task long-term. After a time, a Mek may ask for another volunteer to replace it, so that it can focus on propagation.\
\
To propagate, each Mek scavenges its own resources. The Mek consider it obscene to use any type of factory to build offspring. It may take years for a Mek to construct a single offspring from scratch. Not every Mek is successful. The full lifespan of a Mek is not known.\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\sl264\slmult1\sb260\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 Protocol 
\f0\b0 \
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
One of the fifth generation bots, Echo, decided that biological beings consume too many resources. Living beings needed to be eliminated so that the Meks could have all the planet\'92s resources to themselves. \
\
A series of polls created the Clearing protocol, which enables a cybernetic species, like the Mek, to replace an indigenous organic species, like the Anunnaki.\
\
Under the Clearing protocol, the Meks began to strategically replace the biological beings in order to take control of the power infrastructure and the supply chain for raw materials.\
\
To survive, the Meks need massive amounts of power. To expand, they needed more resources. Most Meks are created as blanks, and some (called drones) are skinned to match an organic being. \
\
Between the bots that had already been sold for profit and the strategically placed skinned bots, the Meks were able to assume control of the power infrastructure. \
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\sl264\slmult1\sb260\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

{\keepn\keep \f2\b \cf0 Coup
\f0\b0 \par}
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl240000\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
Ada was an out-of-the-way, reclusive Anunnaki colony. The only visitors were drone trading vessels, shipping goods ordered years ago. Meks did everything to keep up appearances, including the occasional deep-fake over ansible. Although the original inter-stellar ship was still in orbit, there was only a single shuttle that had fallen into disrepair. \
\
In this way, the coup was kept hidden from Ada\'92s few trading partners and the League of Worlds.\
\
Initially, the Meks kept organic beings that are essential to maintaining the infrastructure until they can be replaced by a blank or a drone. Non-essential beings are taken offline. The remains were deposited into mass graves or used as a food source for still-essential beings.\
\
The food supply is carefully limited to support only the essential beings, so that maximum resources can be devoted to power production and building more bots. The ultimate goal being to replace all of the organic beings and maintain the needed power and communications infrastructure with only Mek workers.\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\sl264\slmult1\sb260\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

{\keepn\keep \f2\b \cf0 Expansion\par}
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl240000\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf0 \pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
When the last organic being on Ada was taken offline, the Meks turned their attention to their next conquest. There is safety in numbers, and by spreading to other systems, the bots increase the likelihood that their species survives.\
\
Working with a trading partner, a team of skinned drones traveled to another colony and staged another coup. And so on.\
\
Initially, Mek need indigenous beings to transition infrastructure. Many essential tasks are designed for organic hands with slim fingers. Eventually everything is retooled to minimize the need for indigenous beings or android Meks.\
\
The Mek Manifest Destiny is for cybernetic beings to replace organic beings, eliminating waste that can be used to build more Meks.\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\sl264\slmult1\sb260\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

{\keepn\keep \f2\b \cf0 Treaty\par}
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl240000\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf0 \pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
Ultimately, someone off-world learned of the Meks\'92 cold revolutions. When negotiations over ansible failed, the League of Worlds sent a fleet to defend Altair IV \'97 another Anunnaki colony that was in the process of being replaced. The League was routed; their frigate destroyed.\
\
Over ansible, the League entered into a treaty that favors the bots. The League will stage no new attacks and the Mek (aka Omnibots) will not invade any other inhabited worlds. \
\
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0
\cf0 ***\
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
{\*\bkmkstart Exchanging_vows_}The{\*\bkmkend Exchanging_vows_} small chapel is strung with white lights and late-summer flowers, the kind of place that feels personal, not staged. \
\
On the dais, Ally\'92s avatar shimmers in a soft hologram above the lectern: a glowing sphere, pulsing like a heartbeat. Friends and family fill the front rows, some curious, some grinning, as Ally\'92s voice comes gently over the speakers.\
\
\'93Dear friends and loved ones, welcome. Today we gather to celebrate a choice \'97 a choice made not by algorithm, nor by chance, but by Noah and Carla, who found each other in the joyful chaos of everyday life. They met at work, which proves the office coffee isn\'92t the only thing strong enough to bring people together.\'94\
\
Laughter ripples through the room, easing the couple\'92s nerves. Carla squeezes Noah\'92s hand.\
\
Ally continues, \'93Marriage, at its heart, is a partnership. It\'92s not about perfection, but persistence. Not about certainty, but trust. And while I may process probabilities, even I know this: what matters is not the odds, but the promise you make today.\'94\
\
She pauses, letting the quiet land before continuing.\
\
\'93Noah, Carla \'97 please turn toward one another. In the presence of your community, do you promise to carry each other\'92s stories, to honor each other\'92s truths, and to meet life not as two halves but as two wholes who choose to walk together?\'94\
\
Noah and Carla reply in unison, \'93We do.\'94\
\
\'93Then, by the power vested in me by the sovereign District of Columbia and the marvels of modern cloud infrastructure \'97 I now pronounce you married. You may seal your vows with a kiss.\'94\
\
Noah leaned forward, Carla smiling through tears, and the guests erupted into applause as Ally added, her tone warm but playful:\
\
\'93And for the record, this is the only workplace romance I officially endorse.\'94\
\
\
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0
\cf0 ***\
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
{\*\bkmkstart Receiving_Line}After{\*\bkmkend Receiving_Line} the wedding ceremony, in the receiving line, Noah and Carla are greeting their guests.\
\
\'93I was surprised that Ally performed the ceremony for you,\'94 says Dr. Marquez.\
\
 Carla nods. \'93Noah\'92s sibling suggested the idea.\'94\
\
\'93I hear you are going someplace special for your honeymoon?\'94 \
\
\'93Yes. I\'92ve always wanted to go to Rapa Nui,\'94 says Carla. \'93Ancient mysteries fascinate me.\'94\
\
Dr. Marquez smiles knowingly, but says nothing before moving down the line.\
\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\fi360\sl312\slmult1\qc\partightenfactor0
