\'93{\*\bkmkstart The_Happiest_Place_On_Earth}I{\*\bkmkend The_Happiest_Place_On_Earth} have seen what they eat for dinner,\'94 says Celeste, \'93but I had no idea how much food Terrans produce.\'94\
\
Leto and Celeste are standing in the doorway of a Wegmans Food Market. The security escorts are hovering just outside, heads on a slow swivel.\
\
Just past the door is a chrome archway equipped with wide, swinging gates.\
\
\'93I can feel a magnetic field,\'94 says Celeste. \'94I think we are being scanned.\'94\
\
\'93Everyone has to pay for food here,\'94 Leto says, \'93the field must be looking for items.\'94\
\
Lights on the archway start to blink, and the Vanir couple stop, confused.\
\
One of the escort officers steps up and hands Celeste a cash card. \'93You need a form of payment to enter. Peter gave us that for expenses. Tap the screen on the gate with the card.\'94\
\
They loosen their cloaks as they enter the store. Looking around, they see bots refilling produce and stocking shelves. One bot is whistling as it rolls down an aisle, seeking shoppers with questions.\
\
\'93Should we buy something?\'94 voices Celeste in a soft tone.\
\
\'93I do not know. We cannot eat Terran food.\'94\
\
\'93Is there something we could get for Jill and Peter?\'94\
\
\'93They eat a lot of that small round fruit.\'94\
\
\'93Grapes?\'94\
\
\'93Yes,\'94 replies Leto, raising his voice, \'93where are the grapes?\'94\
\
Detecting a question, the whistling bot rolls up and displays a map of the store. The map shows a route to the produce aisle.\
\
The shopping car bot rolls around and in front of them \'97 already on route to the grapes. Celeste and Leto tag along.\
\
Celeste rummages through a table stacked with bags of grapes and selects one that doesn\'92t look too big. Placing it in the cart, the bot dings and displays a price: $70.20.\
\
\'93Is that a lot?\'94 she asks Leto. \
\
\'93No idea. I am sure it will be fine.\'94\
\
Strolling around the store, the couple marvel at the variety and quantity of food. Bots whiz by, pulling items from the shelves into their baskets. \
\
When they circle back to the turnstiles, the cart asks \'93Confirm purchase of $70.20?\'94\
\
\'93Yes,\'94 says Celeste.\
\
\'93Deliver to address linked to payment method?\'94\
\
\'93Yes,\'94 she says.\
\
\'93Print or email receipt?\'94\
\
\'93Print?\'94\
\
A strip of paper spools through a slot on the bot, which Celeste collects.\
\
The cart rolls out the door. A bot wearing a reflective \'93Helping Hands\'94 vest signals, and a drone appears. The bot pulls out straps from inside the cart and attaches them to the hovering drone.\
\
\'93I would not want that job,\'94 says Leto, \'93those propeller blades look lethal.\'94\
\
With the container that lined the inside of the cart secured, the drone lifts off and flies in the general direction of Jill and Peter\'92s house.\
\
The escort officer says, \'93The drone will be there in no time. We should move along ourselves. You don\'92t want to be late for school.\'94\
\
A few minutes later, the drone lands behind a fence near Jill and Peter\'92s back door. A moment later, the drone flies back toward the store with the empty strap in its claw.\
\
